  "texts": [
    "This also matches the conclusions drawn about time as a way to solve any contradictions expressed by way of paradoxes or oxymora.",
    "156 It also corresponds to Oscar Wilde's remark that \"paradox is the way of truth,\" 157 or perhaps, of at least a 4D truth.",
    "A similar hidden hint may be found in Shakespeare's Hamlet, in which he wrote: \"This was some time a paradox, but now the time gives it proof.\"",
